						               													<description>-Phantom thief laughs, detective roars. The battle over the hidden treasure.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is a mystery board game for two players in which the detective and the phantom thief can enjoy a brain battle over the treasure. Planning and production is led by board game designer Kengo Otsuka. Character designer Tatsuro Iwamoto(&amp;#229;&amp;#178;&amp;#169;&amp;#229;&amp;#133;&amp;#131;&amp;#232;&amp;#190;&amp;#176;&amp;#233;&amp;#131;&amp;#142;), whose works include the &amp;quot;Ace Attorney&amp;quot; series, designed the characters for the cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The novel included with the game, which is a prequel to the main game, was written by Takeshi Yamazaki(&amp;#229;&amp;#177;&amp;#177;&amp;#239;&amp;#168;&amp;#145;&amp;#229;&amp;#137;&amp;#155;), scenario director of the &amp;quot;Ace Attorney&amp;quot; series.&amp;#10;The well-crafted worldview is appealing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rules are simple. Turn over a card from a deck of your choice and place it in front of the treasure.&amp;#10;The phantom thief aims to steal the treasure, while the detective discovers who the phantom thief is disguised as.&amp;#10;The key is observation. Keep thinking, &amp;quot;Why did he put it there?&amp;quot; and keep thinking &amp;quot;Why did he put it there?&amp;#10;-Every choice you make is being watched by your enemies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On the phantom thief's side...&amp;#10;Where is the real treasure hidden?&amp;#10;How and when should they steal it so that their disguise will not be revealed?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On the detective's side&amp;#10;How should the cards be arranged to protect the real treasure?&amp;#10;Who is the phantom thief disguised as among the six suspects?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Although what you do on your turn is simple, various thoughts intersect with each other.&amp;#10;It is a game of deduction and psychological warfare.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Planning and executive producer is board game designer  Kengo &amp;#197;&amp;#140;tsuka (&amp;#229;&amp;#164;&amp;#167;&amp;#229;&amp;#161;&amp;#154;&amp;#229;&amp;#129;&amp;#165;&amp;#229;&amp;#144;&amp;#190;).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
